Competition: Mundialito

Season: 1980             
Round: Group
Group: A

* Uruguay December 30 1980-January 10 1981. All games played in Montevideo. 
* All former World Cup winners were invited to celebrate the 50-year existence of the competition in the country where the first one was held (and the first winners came from).  The Netherlands, runners-up in the two previous World Cups, replaced England.

12/30/1980; Uruguay; 2-0; Netherlands; Estadio Centenario, Montevideo, Uruguay; Enrique Labo; 65000
Ramos 31, Victorino 45;
Uruguay: Rodríguez; Moreira, Olivera, De León, Martínez; Krasouski, De la Peña, Paz; Ramos, Victorino, Morales (Vargas 75)
Netherlands: Doesburg; Wijnstekers, Spelbos (Valke 64), W.van der Kerkhof, Brandts; Jol, Peters, Hovenkamp; R. van der Kerkhof (van Mierlo 46), Vermeulen, Kist

1/3/1981; Uruguay; 2-0; Italy; Estadio Centenario, Montevideo, Uruguay; Emilio Guruceta; 55000
Morales (pk) 67, Victorino;
Uruguay: Rodriguez; Moreira, Olivera, De León, Martínez; Krasouski, De la Peña, Paz; Ramos, Victorino, Morales (Diogo 69)
